1
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:05,080
Bye, then. Lovely meeting you.
Sorry about the mess!

2
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:07,680
Whoa!

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,840
You think I'd just let you leave
without me, huh?

4
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:14,560
After what we've just been through?

5
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:17,480
Yeah, but you've got the Egyptian people
to rule, Queen Nefertiti,

6
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:20,760
they'll need reassuring after that
weapon-bearing giant alien locust attack

7
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:22,440
we just stopped rather brilliantly...

8
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,520
-(CLOWN HORN SOUNDS)
-Oh, dear!

9
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,120
Sorry, I've got it set to Temporal
News... Ooh, that's interesting.

10
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,240
-Oh, what is?
-Nothing, not interesting, not at...

11
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,520
Ooh-whoo! Never been there, excited!

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,760
DOCTOR: You're not coming!

13
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,840
Craft size, approximately 10 million
square kilometres.

14
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:43,640
A ship the size of Canada
coming at Earth very fast.

15
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:44,840
Any signs of life?

16
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:47,160
We sent up a drone craft.
It took these readings.

17
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,200
Crikey Charlie! Look at that!

18
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,640
Oh, I know somebody who'd love
a look at that.

19
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,800
And the Ponds, we mustn't forget
the Ponds, Nefi.

20
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:56,720
Haven't seen them in ages. I'm riffing.
People usually stop me when I'm riffing.

21
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,200
Or carry on without me.
That's also an option.

22
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:01,080
-Can you communicate with this craft?
-She's with me.

23
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,640
Good question, Nefi.

24
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:07,720
No. No response on any channel,
in any recognised language.

25
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:11,040
If it comes within 10,000 kilometres
of Earth,

26
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,840
we send up missiles.

27
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,440
Oh, Indira. I liked you
before you said missiles.

28
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,320
How long till the ship gets that close?

29
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:21,080
Six hours, 19 minutes.

30
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:22,560
Right. Better get a shift on, then.

31
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:25,640
Leave it with us. Come on then, Nefi.
We're going to need help.

32
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,880
-More stew.
-Where have you been, man?

33
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,480
Seven months. You said
you were popping out for some liquorice.

34
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:35,080
I had two very disappointed dancers
on my hands.

35
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,520
Not that I couldn't manage.

36
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:41,680
Riddell, listen. I found...well...

37
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,920
something.

38
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,560
No, no, no, no, no, no.
I shan't fall for that again.

39
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,800
-What is it?
-I have no idea.

40
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,120
Do you want to find out?

41
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,080
(JANGLING)

42
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,800
-I think it's the fitting.
-Dad, it's not the fitting,

43
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:03,960
it just need a new bulb.

44
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,840
-You're wobbling the ladder.
-I'm not.

45
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,680
I don't want another loft incident.

46
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,320
-How is my side, Brian?
-Perfect, as ever, Amy.

47
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,760
Thank you, Brian.

48
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,160
I don't know what he said to you
to make you marry him.

49
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,960
But he's a lucky man.

50
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,280
(WHOOSHING)

51
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,480
Not here, not now.

52
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,720
You leave the back door open?

53
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,000
-What is he doing?
-I'm going to kill him.

54
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,960
Hello, you weren't busy, were you?

55
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,480
Well, even if you were,
it wasn't as interesting as this...

56
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,600
probably is.

57
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:34,320
Didn't want you to miss it.
Now, just a quick hop.

58
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:40,920
(RUMBLING)

59
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,400
Everybody grab a torch.

60
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:52,160
Spiders.

61
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,760
We don't normally get spiders in space.

62
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,160
What the...

63
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,200
Don't move!

64
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,960
Do you really think I'm that stupid,
I wouldn't notice?

65
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,640
How did you get aboard, hey? Transmat?

66
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:06,600
-Who sent you?
-Doctor... (CLEARS THROAT)

67
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,000
That's my dad.

68
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,720
-Well, frankly, that's outrageous.
-What?

69
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:15,280
You think you can just bring
your dad along without asking?

70
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:18,960
-I'm not a taxi service, you know.
-You materialised around us!

71
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:22,520
Oh. Well, that's fine then.
My mistake. Hello, Brian.

72
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,080
How are you? Nice to meet you. Welcome.

73
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,120
Welcome. This is the gang.
I've got a gang.

74
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,160
Yes. Come on, then, everyone.

75
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:34,680
-Tell him something, quick.
-Yes. Thank you.

76
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,600
I'm not entirely sure what's going on.

77
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:41,600
You know when Amy and I first got
married and we went travelling...

78
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:45,000
-To Thailand.
-More the entirety of space and time.

79
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,840
In that police box.

80
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,640
(LOUD THUDDING)

81
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,520
All right, where are we?
What is that noise?

82
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,480
And hello, 10 months!

83
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:01,600
Orbiting Earth. Well, I say orbiting.
More like pre-crashing.

84
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,880
On a spaceship. Don't know.
And hello, Pond.

85
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,360
Ten months.

86
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,240
Time flies. Never really understood
that phrase.

87
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,320
This is Nefi. This is Riddell.
They're with me.

88
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,400
With you? What, they're "with" you?

89
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,760
Are they the new us?
Is that why we haven't seen you?

90
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,480
No, they're just people.
They're not Ponds.

91
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,640
I thought we might need a gang.
Not really had a gang before.

92
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,280
It's new.

93
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,880
(WHIRRING)

94
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,120
(BEEPING)

95
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,840
-It's coming down.
-What is it?

96
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,640
No idea.

97
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,600
(ALARM BLARING)

98
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,400
(GROWLING)

99
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,600
Not possible.

100
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,640
Run!

101
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,040
(ROARING)

102
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,760
-Doctor!
-I know.

103
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:56,760
Dinosaurs, on a spaceship!

104
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,600
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

105
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,320
(ROARING)

106
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,480
(CRYING OUT)

107
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:46,960
In here!

108
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,640
Oh, dear. Ohhh!

109
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,200
(FOOTSTEPS CRASHING, CREATURES ROARING)

110
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,400
I can take one of them.

111
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,240
Short blow up in the throat.

112
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:12,120
Or not. We just found dinosaurs.
In space! We need to preserve them.

113
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,000
-And who's going to preserve us?
-Shh!

114
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:40,760
Okay, so...how? And whose ship?

115
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,800
DOCTOR: Well there's so much
to discover.

116
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,120
Think how much wiser we'll be
by the end of all this.

117
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,960
Sorry. Sorry.

118
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:51,480
Are you saying dinosaurs
are flying a spaceship?

119
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:54,440
Brian, please. That would be ridiculous.
They're probably just passengers.

120
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:56,560
-Did I mention missiles?
-Missiles?

121
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:00,360
Didn't want to worry you.
Anyway, six hours is a lifetime.

122
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:03,000
Not literally a lifetime.
That's what we're trying to avoid.

123
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,920
And we're all really clever. Ooh.

124
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,480
Let's see what we can find out.

125
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,840
Come on.

126
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,520
Ugh...

127
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,960
How many dinosaurs do you think
are on here?

128
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,400
(BUZZING)

129
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,040
Oh, well done, whoever you are.

130
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,800
Looking for engines.

131
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,520
Thank you, computer. Look at that.

132
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:32,160
Different sections
have different engines,

133
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,760
but these look like
the primary clusters.

134
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:37,640
Where are we now, computer?
We need to get down to these engines.

135
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,760
-What happened?
-Oh, great.

136
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,760
Find out...

137
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:47,480
What?

138
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,240
We're outside. We're on a beach.

139
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:52,760
Teleport... Oh, I hate teleports!

140
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:55,200
-Must have activated on my voice.
-Ah, yes.

141
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,720
Well, thank you, Arthur C Clarke.

142
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:01,760
Teleport, obviously. I mean,
we're on a spaceship with dinosaurs.

143
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:05,960
Why wouldn't there be a teleport?
In fact, why don't we just teleport now?

144
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,280
-Is he all right?
-No, he hates travelling.

145
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,840
It makes him really anxious.
He only goes to the paper shop and golf.

146
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,520
What did you bring him for?

147
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:18,840
I didn't! Why can't you just phone ahead
like any normal person?

148
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,520
Somebody tell me where we are. Now!

149
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,040
Well, it's not Earth.

150
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:29,560
Doesn't taste right. Too metallic.

151
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:32,280
-(SQUAWKING)
-Is that a kestrel?

152
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,320
I do hope so.

153
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,640
-The beach is humming.
-Is it?

154
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:40,800
Oh, yes. Well, don't just stand there,
you two. Dig!

155
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,880
I'm going to look at rocks.

156
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,720
-Love a rock.
-Dig with what?

157
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,280
Ah! Well.

158
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,600
-Did you just have that on you?
-Course.

159
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,200
What sort of a man doesn't carry
a trowel?

160
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,640
-Put it on your Christmas list.
-Dad, I'm 31.

161
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:00,280
-I don't have a Christmas list any more.
-I do!

162
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,960
(CLANGING)

163
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,440
There's a floor under this beach.

164
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,720
Doctor!

165
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,360
Doctor!

166
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,920
MAN: Did you hear that?

167
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,800
Did you hear what he called him?
Doctor.

168
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,120
After all this time.

169
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,080
-Doctor!
-Bring them to me.

170
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,480
Doctor!

171
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,240
There are clearly more than
just two of these creatures.

172
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,520
Hey, put that away. I need you sober.

173
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,720
It's medicinal.

174
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,880
And I don't take orders from females.

175
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,560
NEFERTITI: Then learn.

176
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:41,840
Any man who speaks to me that way,
I execute.

177
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,840
You're very welcome to try.

178
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,640
Sorry, what was your name again?

179
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,920
Lady of the Two Lands,

180
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,880
wife of the great King Amenhotep.

181
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,040
Queen Nefertiti of Egypt.

182
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:58,480
-I'll be damned.
-Oh, my God. Queen Nefertiti?

183
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:03,040
I learned all about you at school.
You're awesome. Big fan. High five.

184
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,520
Yeah, a bit behind on that.

185
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,800
-You're really famous.
-Shh! Listen.

186
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,640
(LOW SNARLING)

187
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,160
(GROWLING)

188
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,640
Okay.

189
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,800
AX a guess, 1. rex.

190
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,360
Not yet full size.
We're in the middle of a dinosaur nest.

191
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,440
I propose a retreat.

192
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,480
-Perhaps forwards.
-Agreed.

193
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,320
Just don't wake the baby.

194
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,640
(GROWLING)

195
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,440
(RIDDELL LAUGHING)

196
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,560
Oh, my God.

197
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,840
Who are you, anyway?

198
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:04,160
John Riddell. Big game hunter
in the African plains.

199
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,760
-I'm sure you've heard of me, too.
-No.

200
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,480
Well, you clearly have
some alarming gaps in your education.

201
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:13,440
Or men who hunt defenceless creatures
just don't impact on history.

202
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,720
Face it, she's just way cooler than you.

203
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,920
And you, Amy?

204
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,800
Are you also a queen?

205
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,400
Yes.

206
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,720
Yes, I am.

207
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:28,920
See? Metal floors. Screens in rocks.

208
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,880
It was just a short-range teleport.
We're still on the ship.

209
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,520
-No, we're outside on a beach.
-No, it's part of the ship, Dad.

210
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,680
-Don't be ridiculous.
-Well, it is quite ridiculous.

211
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:39,400
Also, brilliant. That's why
the system teleported us here.

212
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:43,280
I wanted the engines.
This is the engine room!

213
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:46,320
Hydro-generators! Ha!

214
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,680
I have literally no idea
what he's saying.

215
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:52,680
-A spaceship powered by waves.
-Fabulously impossible.

216
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,640
Oh, think of the things we could learn
from this ship

217
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,840
if we managed to stop it
being blown to pieces.

218
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,400
-Plus, not dying.
-Bad news is

219
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,800
can't shut the wave system down
in time. It takes...

220
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,360
It takes way too long.

221
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,480
Well, if these are the engines,
there must be a control room.

222
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,440
Exactly.
That's what we need to find, now.

223
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:11,080
What do we do about the things
that aren't kestrels?

224
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,320
(CREATURES SQUAWKING)

225
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,120
Oh, my lord.

226
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,720
-Are those pterodactyls?
-Yes.

227
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:25,080
On any other occasion, I'd be thrilled.
Exposed on a beach, less than thrilled.

228
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,320
-We should be going.
-Where?

229
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,560
-Definitely away from them.
-That's the plan?

230
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:29,920
-That's the plan.
-Amendments welcome.

231
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,680
Move away from the pterodactyls.

232
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,720
-RORY: I think they might be noticing.
-Amended plan - run!

233
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,480
RORY: Can't we
just teleport or something?

234
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:39,480
No! Local teleports
burned out on arrival.

235
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,040
(PTERODACTYLS SCREECHING)

236
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,000
Ah! There's an opening
in the cliffs over there!

237
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,680
-Come on!
-I'm trying!

238
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,360
Oh!

239
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,520
(SQUAWKING)

240
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,520
-Are you all right?
-Yeah, I'm fine. Oh!

241
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,080
What do we do now?
There's no way back out there.

242
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,360
Through the cave. Come on.

243
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,160
(LOUD THUD)

244
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,080
That suggestion was a work in progress.

245
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,800
-We're trapped.
-Yes, thanks for spelling it out.

246
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,760
Doctor, whatever's down there
is coming this way.

247
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:24,520
Spelling it out is hereditary.
Wonderful!

248
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,320
That sound's getting nearer.

249
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:30,240
(RHYTHMIC THUDDING)

250
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,240
(THUDDING SPEEDS UP)

251
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,040
ROBOT: We're very cross with you.

252
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,560
Bit of weed killer wouldn't go amiss
in here.

253
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:57,720
Whoever was running this vessel
left in a hurry.

254
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,560
Maybe a plague came and took them.

255
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:03,200
-No, there'd be corpses and bones.
-Unless the animals ate them.

256
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:06,920
Whoa, Chuckle Brothers.
Lighten up, would you?

257
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:12,120
(WHIRRING)

258
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,080
How'd you know how to do that?

259
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,000
Well, I've spent enough time
with the Doctor

260
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,360
to know whenever you enter
somewhere new, press buttons.

261
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:20,360
What else have you learned from him?

262
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:23,200
Don't stop at button-pressing.

263
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:28,280
-MAN: 777 years.
-Data records.

264
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,400
-Ship's owners?
-Could be.

265
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,480
Come on, help us out.

266
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,200
...remain cryogenic.

267
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:45,360
Whilst they sleep, I will continue
to work, being careful to...

268
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:48,560
How about a picture? Hmm?
Come on. For me?

269
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,440
...far beyond our land.

270
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,920
Look!

271
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,480
Oh, it's beautiful!

272
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:57,080
I can't tell how far we have come.

273
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:01,160
Far enough to avoid
the destructive impact

274
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:03,240
forecast for our planet.

275
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:06,480
Far enough for me to feel
a profound sense of loss.

276
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,400
What is that?

277
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,480
Silurian.

278
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,800
ROBOT: You're going straight
on the naughty step.

279
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,400
What's the escape plan?

280
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,520
Why do we want to escape?

281
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,560
They have us hostage.

282
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:25,160
They're taking us somewhere.
We might learn from it.

283
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:28,880
Ah, you see? So clever.
I've missed you, Rory.

284
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:31,120
-Don't do that.
-What if they kill us?

285
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:34,920
They wouldn't do that. You're not
going to kill us, are you, rusty?

286
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:36,720
ROBOT 1: Who are you calling rusty?

287
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,280
Have you seen yourself lately?

288
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,600
You try being on this ship
for two millennia.

289
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,520
See how your paintwork does.

290
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,560
ROBOT 2: Don't listen to him. He's just
being mean because we captured him.

291
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,200
Oh, my goodness!

292
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,440
-Whoa!
-Ooh!

293
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,160
Herbivore, Brian.
Don't panic. Triceratops.

294
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,680
Ha! Beautiful.

295
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:57,800
ROBOT 2: Shall I shoot it?

296
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,240
ROBOT 1: We're not supposed to shoot
the creatures, stupid.

297
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:03,000
-ROBOT 2: Stop calling me stupid.
-"Rah!" yourself.

298
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,680
Hello, cutie-pie.

299
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:08,360
Who's a lovely Tricey, then, eh?

300
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:11,320
Yes, you are. Yes, you are.

301
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,920
What do I do? What do I do?

302
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:16,440
What's it doing?

303
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,640
You don't have any vegetable matter
in your trousers, do you, Brian?

304
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,960
Only my balls.

305
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,120
-I'm sorry?
-Golf balls.

306
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,720
-Grassy residue.
-What are you carrying those around for?

307
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,640
(SLOBBERING)

308
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,320
Ugh!

309
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,760
Ew! Ah!

310
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:42,280
-DOCTOR: Oh, bless.
-Get it away from me!

311
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,480
-Throw one.
-Really?

312
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,320
Is this what you want? Is it?

313
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,800
And breathe out.

314
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,640
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

315
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:59,280
Right. Take us to your leader.

316
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,360
-Really?
-Too good to resist.

317
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:09,520
Of the 50 species loaded, only one
has had any difficulty surviving.

318
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,560
All the others are thriving

319
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,440
and we expect them to be able
to repopulate.

320
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,960
We're on an ark. A Silurian ark.

321
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:21,800
Lizard-people herding dinosaurs
onto a space ark?

322
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,240
Absolute tommyrot.

323
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:26,760
Only an idiot denies the evidence
of their own eyes.

324
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:29,720
Egyptian queen or not, I shall
put you across my knee and spank you.

325
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,200
-Oh, Lord.
-Try!

326
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:35,120
-And I'll snap your neck in a heartbeat.
-Hmm.

327
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,920
Well, they certainly bred firecrackers
in your time.

328
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,320
Oh, no, no, no.
Please don't start flirting.

329
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,160
I will not have flirting companions.

330
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:44,760
If the Doctor trusts Amy, so do I.

331
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:47,040
Stop doubting her.

332
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,800
-If this ship was built by...
-Silurians, yeah?

333
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,040
Yeah, where are they?

334
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,440
Surprisingly good question.

335
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:00,400
Display life-signs for Homo reptilia.

336
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,720
AMY: Where have they gone?

337
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,480
Perhaps they found another world,
left the ship.

338
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,520
Well, why are the dinosaurs
still on board?

339
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:14,360
And why is the ship coming back
to Earth? It doesn't make sense.

340
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:16,280
What's changed between then and now?

341
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:17,960
Wait, computer?

342
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:20,400
Show me the ship at launch
with all life signals.

343
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:25,200
Now show me the ship today
with all life signals.

344
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,680
Thousands less.

345
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:29,600
But why? I mean...

346
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,760
Show me both images, then and now,
side by side.

347
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:32,840
What are you looking for?

348
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:35,840
Okay, two images, spot the difference.
What changed?

349
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,000
What happened to the Silurians?

350
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:41,040
-The centre.
-Computer, zoom in to the centre.

351
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,280
AMY: Oh, no.
RIDDELL: What is it?

352
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,680
Another spacecraft.

353
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,440
This ship's been boarded before.

354
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:03,120
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

355
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,440
Love what you've done with the place
down here.

356
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:08,320
MAN: Let him in. Open the gate.

357
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:18,520
It's fine. It's fine.

358
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:22,080
-He's not interested in you.
-Look.

359
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:26,880
-You need to learn some manners.
-No, you need to learn some manners.

360
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,040
No, you do.

361
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:31,600
No. You do, Mr Manners.

362
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:37,200
Fantasia in F Minorfor four hands.

363
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,320
-You know it.
-Know it?

364
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:44,080
Say hello to hands three and four.

365
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,720
Schubert kept tickling me
to try and put me off.

366
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:49,960
Franz the Hands.
Oh, that takes me back.

367
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:53,800
Well, this is...cosy.

368
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,720
It's fate you came.

369
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,120
Is it?

370
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:04,120
-I'm the Doctor.
-Yes, I know.

371
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:06,880
I'm Solomon.

372
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,160
What's that?

373
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:14,800
System malfunction. Ignore it.

374
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,000
What happened to you?

375
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,040
I was attacked.

376
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,240
Three raptors. They cornered me.

377
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:26,320
The robots rescued me
but it was nearly too late.

378
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,680
Ah, yes. The robots.

379
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:33,600
-They're...unusual.
-I got them cheap.

380
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,360
From a concession on Aluria 7.

381
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:40,000
The robots did as best they could
with my legs but...

382
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,680
you can help me so much more.

383
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:49,920
Oh, a doctor doctor, I see.

384
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,040
Let's have a look.

385
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:59,960
They chewed through a part of the bone
in my legs.

386
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:06,280
Yes. Very nasty.

387
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,280
But you can repair them?

388
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:17,240
If you tell me how you came by
so many dinosaurs.

389
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:25,880
-Injure the older one.
-What?

390
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,640
(CRYING OUT)

391
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,680
It's all right, Dad.
It's okay. It's okay.

392
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,760
I don't respond well
to violence, Solomon.

393
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,880
And I don't like questions, Doctor.

394
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,440
You boarded without my permission.

395
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:51,400
Now, fix me
or the next bolt will be fatal.

396
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:57,440
I will take you apart cog by cog
and melt you down when all this is over.

397
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,800
Oh, I'm so scared.

398
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,800
Actually, I might be.
A little bit of oil just came out.

399
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:07,480
Now, stay still. It's just a burn.
It's nothing serious.

400
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,640
-What's that?
-While you carry a trowel,

401
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:10,720
I carry a Med-Pack.

402
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,640
It's all about the pockets
in our family.

403
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:14,800
This is an ice patch, it cools the skin.

404
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,880
Never seen one of those.

405
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,800
Yeah, I look out for cool stuff
wherever we go.

406
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,880
Some people it's cars
and hardware, for me,

407
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:23,160
-it is nursing supplies.
-(GROANING)

408
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:26,240
-Mmm.
-Now, painkiller.

409
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,800
Now, this won't hurt.

410
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,360
Ow!

411
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:32,280
I lied.
It won't hurt from now on, though.

412
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,600
All right, you.

413
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,720
-You're done.
-Thanks.

414
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,720
That's all right.

415
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,880
You get to see my awesome nursing skills
in action for once.

416
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:43,440
(PHONE RINGING)

417
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:45,280
-What's that?
-Your phone's ringing.

418
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,520
-In space?
-You get used to it.

419
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,760
I have to take this. The wife.

420
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,880
-Hello, missus.
-Where are you?

421
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,680
Still on board.

422
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:58,440
Met some pterodactyls and some rusty
robots that I'm going to melt down.

423
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,520
Rory, this is a Silurian ship.

424
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:05,120
How did you get on board, Doctor?

425
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:10,840
Oh, I never talk about myself
with a gun pointed at me.

426
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,080
Let's talk about you.

427
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:16,840
Your cosy little craft,
embedded in a vast old ship.

428
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,920
-You're very observant.
-I'm a Sagittarius.

429
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,840
Probably.

430
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:25,880
I'm transporting it
to the Roxbourne Peninsula.

431
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,800
Commerce colony?

432
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:29,360
You're a trader.

433
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:33,280
I search out opportunities for profit
across the nine galaxies.

434
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:35,320
Ah, the purple light.

435
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,400
That's what it was.

436
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,480
(BEEPING)

437
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:41,000
An IV system, identifying value,

438
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:45,600
the database of everything across space
and time allocated a market value.

439
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:48,760
Argos for the universe.

440
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:53,000
You were trying to find out
how much I'm worth.

441
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,920
Would you like to know?

442
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:11,600
You don't exist.

443
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,000
It's never done that.

444
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,720
That's me. Worthless.

445
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:20,280
Unlike these creatures
you have on board.

446
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,480
Very valuable,

447
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:25,280
-given they're extinct.
-(WHIRRING)

448
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,320
(GROANS)

449
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:29,880
Done.

450
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,880
Sit up. Very slowly.

451
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:34,680
Doctor! Amy.

452
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,840
I need to take this.

453
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,280
-Amy.
-This is an ark,

454
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:43,840
built by the Silurians.
They were looking for another planet.

455
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,880
-Where are they now?
-None on board.

456
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:49,000
I mean, thousands of stasis pods,
all empty.

457
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:50,360
I'll see you soon.

458
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,120
(SIGHS)

459
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:57,360
Be ready.

460
00:24:57,560 --> 00:25:00,400
The pain in my legs is gone.

461
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:03,760
I can move them. Thank you, Doctor.

462
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,440
What did you do to the Silurians?

463
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:11,840
We ejected them.

464
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:16,800
The robots woke them from cryosleep
a handful at a time

465
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,720
and jettisoned them from the airlocks.

466
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,280
We must have left a trail
of dust and bone.

467
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:26,080
Because you wanted the dinosaurs.

468
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,120
Their ship crossed my path.

469
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:32,400
I sent out a distress signal,
they let me board,

470
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:37,640
but when I saw the cargo,
things became more complex.

471
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,880
Piracy, then genocide.

472
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:44,680
-Very emotive words, Doctor.
-Oh, I'm a very emotive man.

473
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,880
The lizards wouldn't negotiate.

474
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,200
I made them a generous offer.

475
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:53,000
The creatures onboard this ship
are not objects to be sold or traded.

476
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,640
I feel like you're judging me.

477
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:57,160
You said Roxbourne Peninsula,
so why are you heading to Earth?

478
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:59,040
You're on the wrong course.

479
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,640
Oh.

480
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,680
You don't know how. Ha.

481
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:09,360
Brilliant.

482
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:12,440
You couldn't change the pre-programmed
course without instructions,

483
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:14,400
the ship defaulted, returned home.

484
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:16,800
Oh, dear.

485
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:21,120
The Silurians outwitted you,
even after you massacred them.

486
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:23,160
So now

487
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,680
you're a prisoner on the ship
you hijacked.

488
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,640
Not now you're here.

489
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:30,120
You're going to help me
to where I want to go, Doctor.

490
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:33,400
Little bit of news, Solomon.
You're being targeted by missiles.

491
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,240
Get off this ship.

492
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,560
While you still can.

493
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:45,560
You think I believe that?

494
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:48,920
You just want them for yourself.

495
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,800
You won't profit from me, Doctor.

496
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:54,280
Don't ever judge me by your standards.

497
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:59,560
Well, don't just stand there, Rory.
Hey, he wants to see you.

498
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:01,520
Dad, up.

499
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,000
-What are we doing?
-Just do exactly as I do!

500
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,720
-Doctor, no!
-Geronimo!

501
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,360
(ROARING)

502
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:18,480
-Did you call?
-SOLOMON: What are you doing?

503
00:27:18,560 --> 00:27:19,640
Stop them!

504
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:22,720
-All right. Don't shout.
-SOLOMON: Useless machines!

505
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:29,560
Go, Tricey! Run like the wind!

506
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:30,880
(SNORTS)

507
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:34,000
Oh!

508
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:37,440
Quick, how do you start a triceratops?

509
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:42,400
-There they are.
-I know. I saw them before you.

510
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:46,640
Hang on a minute. Tricey, fetch!

511
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:49,960
Ha-ha! Good boy!

512
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,840
Yee-ha!

513
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:55,280
Come on, Tricey!

514
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:58,880
(WHOOPING)

515
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:03,960
-They've stolen a dinosaur!
-I can see that.

516
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:08,120
Come on, Tricey! Faster, baby!

517
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,120
ALL: Whoa!

518
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:19,360
ROBOT 1: They're turning off!
We're losing them!

519
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:22,320
ROBOT 2: Which way did they go?
ROBOT 1: I thought you were looking.

520
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:24,600
ROBOT 2: No, now they've got away.

521
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:26,960
ROBOT 1: We definitely
used to be faster.

522
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,400
I'm riding a dinosaur! On a spaceship!

523
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,520
-I know!
-I only came round to fix your light!

524
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,520
Come on, Tricey!

525
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:40,360
Where are the brakes?

526
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,080
(ALL SHOUTING)

527
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,920
Ahh! (THUDDING)

528
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:52,280
(ALL GROANING)

529
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:11,520
Good! That worked. Okay.

530
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:14,680
Uh, where are we now? Ooh!

531
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:19,440
Incoming message from Earth!
Hello, Earth! How are things?

532
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:23,280
Doctor, the ship's coming through
the atmosphere.

533
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:26,640
- I have to start the missile programme.
-No. No, no, no, don't do that.

534
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,400
Everything's completely
under control here.

535
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:30,960
Turning round any moment. Need a bit
of wriggle room on the timings.

536
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:33,480
-I can't do that.
-You can. Of course you can!

537
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:35,200
A tiny bit more time. Indira, please.

538
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:37,160
This ship contains the most
precious cargo.

539
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:40,320
My only responsibility
Is the Earth's safety.

540
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,360
I'm launching the missiles.

541
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:43,880
Goodbye, Doctor.

542
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:45,640
No, Indira!

543
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,680
Hey, come back! Please!

544
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:50,040
MAN: (ON PA) Target identified.

545
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,520
Navigation systems locking
on to target.

546
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:54,760
Missile launch procedure initiated.

547
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,440
Estimated impact, 30 minutes.

548
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:03,000
Now, these are what we need.
Dinosaur protection.

549
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:06,480
No weapons.

550
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:10,600
Anaesthetic?

551
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,240
These are stun guns.

552
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:15,240
-You're almost clever.
-Enough to make a dinosaur take a nap.

553
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,640
Even the Doctor couldn't object to that.

554
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:20,360
You and the Doctor, are you his queen?

555
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:22,680
No, no, I'm Rory's queen. Wife.

556
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:24,640
Wife. I'm his wife.

557
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,160
Please don't tell him I said
I was his queen.

558
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,240
I'll never hear the end of it.

559
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:30,320
And the Doctor, does he have a queen?

560
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,720
I thought you had a husband.

561
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,920
A male equivalent of a sleeping potion.

562
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,400
You clearly need a man of action
and excitement.

563
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,680
One with a very large weapon.

564
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:41,080
(WHIRRING)

565
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:45,640
So, human sleeping potion
or walking innuendo.

566
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:46,800
Take your pick.

567
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:48,240
(BEEPING)

568
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:50,080
DOCTOR: That's very bad indeed.

569
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:51,680
Completely unhelpful.

570
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:53,880
RORY: Doesn't this ship have
any defence systems installed?

571
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:56,120
Good thinking, Rory!

572
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,800
Computer, show us weapons
and defence systems.

573
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:03,360
Oh. That was a waste of time, wasn't it?
Getting my hopes up like that.

574
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:05,000
What ship doesn't have weapons?

575
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:07,800
The ancient species, Rory -
still full of hope.

576
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:08,960
What about the control deck?

577
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:12,120
You said we should go to
the control deck next.

578
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,800
It's too late.
It won't make any difference.

579
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,000
-We could at least try.
-It won't work, Rory.

580
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:17,720
-The missiles are locked on.
-So, what,

581
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:20,000
-we're just giving up?
-I don't know.

582
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:23,440
I don't know!

583
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:28,120
SOLOMON: You were telling
the truth, Doctor.

584
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:30,720
Earth has launched missiles.

585
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,280
This vessel is too clumsy
to outrun them

586
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:34,880
but I have my own ship.

587
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:38,040
You won't get your precious cargo
on board, though. Just be you

588
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,960
and your metal tantrum machines.

589
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,880
-We do not have tantrums/!
-Shut up!

590
00:31:48,360 --> 00:31:49,880
You're right, Doctor.

591
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:53,520
I can't keep the dinosaurs
and live myself.

592
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:57,720
But I had the IV system scan
the entire ship.

593
00:31:57,920 --> 00:32:00,440
And it found something even more
valuable.

594
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,840
Utterly unique.

595
00:32:03,480 --> 00:32:05,560
I don't know where you found it

596
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,680
or how you got it here

597
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:10,560
-but I want it.
-I don't know what you're talking about.

598
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,840
Earth Queen Nefertiti of Egypt.

599
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:18,240
A face stamped across history.

600
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:21,560
Give her to me
and I'll let the rest of you live.

601
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:27,160
No.

602
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:32,680
You think I won't punish those
who get in my way?

603
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:34,840
Whatever they're worth?

604
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,840
(ROARING)

605
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:47,080
(TRICERATOPS HOWLING)

606
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,760
(GROANING SOFTLY)

607
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,080
You must be very proud.

608
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:25,480
Bring her to me or the robots will
make their way through your corpses.

609
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:32,440
-Bring her now.
-No.

610
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:46,080
-What are you doing?
-I demanded to be brought here.

611
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,840
No. No, no, no, no. No way.

612
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:49,760
It isn't your choice, Doctor, it's mine.

613
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:52,320
Listen to me. If you go with him,
I can't guarantee your safety.

614
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:56,040
-You saved my people. I am in your debt.
-No.

615
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:58,120
No debts. You don't owe me anything.

616
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:00,800
-Then I do it of my own will.
-Nefi! Nefi!

617
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:02,040
No!

618
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:04,400
-Take her, I shoot you.
-Put your weapon down.

619
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,160
Let me make my choice.

620
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:08,080
Do it, boy.

621
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:22,440
My bounty increases.

622
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:26,360
And what an extraordinary bounty
you are.

623
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,200
Never touch me.

624
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,880
I like my possessions to have spirit.

625
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,960
It means I can have fun breaking them.

626
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:44,840
And I will break you in
with immense pleasure.

627
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:50,600
Thank you, Doctor.

628
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:53,680
Computer, take us back to my ship.

629
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,520
(ALARM BLARING)

630
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,880
AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE:
Hostile targeting in progress.

631
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:03,320
Hostile targeting in progress.

632
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:05,600
Hostile targeting in progress.

633
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:08,240
Hostile targeting in progress.

634
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:10,360
Hostile targeting in progress.

635
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:13,880
-Bingo.
-What is it? Doctor?

636
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:16,920
Okay. Control deck.

637
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,080
RORY: So, what's the plan?

638
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,560
Come on.

639
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,960
The missiles are locked on to us.
We can't outrun them.

640
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:26,360
We have to save the dinosaurs
and get Nefertiti back from Solomon.

641
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,440
Isn't it obvious?

642
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:28,920
Uh, it's sort of the opposite
of obvious.

643
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,760
Seventeen minutes
before the missiles hit.

644
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:32,200
We need to turn this ship around.

645
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:34,640
RORY: You said it was too late,
that there wasn't any time.

646
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:38,480
Ah, yes, but I didn't have this plan
then, did I? Riddell?

647
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,240
Keep an eye out for dinosaurs.

648
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:41,760
I was rather hoping you'd say that.

649
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:45,040
No killing any.
Rory, Brian, get rid of the cobwebs.

650
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:53,800
Come on. Come on! We're not moving.

651
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,520
He's magnetised us.

652
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:00,760
We can't move away.

653
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:08,480
(RAPTOR TRILLING)

654
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:11,320
(GROWLING)

655
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,440
Keep walking, big chap.

656
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,760
(CROAKING)

657
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:24,720
(ALL ROARING)

658
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:28,000
Hell's teeth. That's really not fair.

659
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,960
MAN: (ON PA) Missile target
will be reached in 11 minutes.

660
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:37,200
No, don't be like that.
Really unhelpful.

661
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:39,280
-What's the matter?
-Parallel pilot compartment,

662
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:42,080
it's bio-configured, needs two operators
of the same gene chain.

663
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:45,040
That's why Solomon couldn't change
the ship's course and neither can we.

664
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,880
-What?
-We can.

665
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:52,120
Me and Rory. We must be the same
gene thingy you just said.

666
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,240
Brian Pond, you are delicious.

667
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:57,000
-I'm not a Pond.
-Of course you are. Sit down.

668
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:58,080
Both of you. Lickety-split.

669
00:36:58,160 --> 00:37:00,760
Ship does all the engineering.
The controls are straightforward.

670
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:03,320
Even a monkey could use them.
Oh, look, they're going to.

671
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:08,560
Guys, come on. Comedy gold.

672
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:10,680
Where's a Silurian audience
when you need one?

673
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:13,760
Anyway, two eyeline screens,
velocity and trajectory.

674
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:14,840
Steer away from the Earth.

675
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:17,720
Try not to bump into the Moon, otherwise
the races who live there will be livid.

676
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:18,800
What?

677
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,480
Primary control's in the arms
of the chairs.

678
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:24,560
Principle's the same as any vehicle.
Eight minutes, 45 seconds.

679
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:29,000
Get us as far away as you can.

680
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,080
Right.

681
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:33,840
Phase two sorted, now for phase one.

682
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,960
(LAUGHING) No, phase two
comes after phase one.

683
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:38,640
Humans, you're so linear.
Shine a torch in here.

684
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:40,560
-What are you doing?
-Mixing my messages.

685
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:41,880
How's the job?

686
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:44,200
We're about to be hit by missiles
and you're asking me that?

687
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:46,240
I work best when I'm multitasking.
Keep talking.

688
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:47,480
How's the job?

689
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:49,200
-1...gave it up.
-You gave the last one up.

690
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,560
Yeah, well, I can't settle.

691
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,800
Every minute I'm listening out
for that stupid Tardis...

692
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:56,240
-Right, so it's my fault now, is it?
-I can't not wait for you. Even now.

693
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:58,440
And they're getting longer, you know,
the gaps between your visits.

694
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:00,600
-Are they?
-I think you're weaning us off you.

695
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:02,440
I'm not. I promise.

696
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:06,920
I really promise.
The others, they're not you,

697
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:09,200
but you're more, you have lives,
each other.

698
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:10,960
I thought that's what we agreed.

699
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:14,080
I know. I just worry there'll come
a time when you never turn up,

700
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:16,360
that something will have happened to you
and I'll still be waiting,

701
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,520
never knowing.

702
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:20,080
No, come on, Pond.

703
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:23,680
-You'll be there till the end of me.
-Or vice-versa.

704
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,960
Done.

705
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,600
Doctor, this is a two-man job.

706
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:39,280
What are you doing?

707
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:41,080
I'm easily worth two men.

708
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:42,520
You can help, too, if you like.

709
00:38:44,920 --> 00:38:46,520
(BEEPING)

710
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:49,080
A-ha!

711
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:51,200
Doctor, what are you going to do...

712
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,640
(SCREEN BEEPING)

713
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:02,840
(GROWLING)

714
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:04,640
Quickens the blood, doesn't it?

715
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,920
The sooner this lot go back
to being extinct, the better.

716
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,520
You know what I want more than anything?

717
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:09,920
Lessons in gender politics?

718
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,920
A dinosaur tooth to take home.

719
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:19,400
Dinosaurs ahead, a lady at my side,
about to be blown up,

720
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,320
I'm not sure I've ever been happier.

721
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:23,040
Shut up and shoot.

722
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,800
Duck!

723
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:38,280
(BOTH GRUNTING)

724
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:43,000
Uh, I'm flying a spaceship.

725
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:44,960
-Rory?
-Hmm?

726
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:47,960
-We're flying a spaceship!
-I know! (LAUGHS)

727
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,920
The ship's trajectory is changing.

728
00:39:55,040 --> 00:39:56,440
This makes no difference.

729
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:59,720
The missiles have locked on.
How long till target?

730
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:03,280
Seven minutes.

731
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,040
No!

732
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:09,080
That's it, that's it!

733
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:12,160
That's it, that's it.
Me, me, me, me, me!

734
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:14,160
Yes, yes!

735
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:16,880
It's better than golf.

736
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:21,960
Hello! Having trouble leaving?

737
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:26,120
ROBOTS: (POWERING DOWN)
# Daisy, Daisy

738
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,400
# Give me your answer, do #

739
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:30,560
Ship's still magnetised.
Couldn't bear to lose you.

740
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:32,280
Release my ship, Doctor.

741
00:40:33,080 --> 00:40:35,960
Or I kill this precious little object.

742
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,160
(SOLOMON GRUNTING)

743
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:44,720
I'm not your possession now,
nor will I ever be.

744
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,840
Now, stay there.

745
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:51,640
Don't mess with Egyptian queens,
Solomon.

746
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:55,560
-I hope you've learnt that now.
-(SOLOMON GRUNTING)

747
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:58,560
-What are you doing?
-Disabling this ship's signal

748
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:00,880
and replacing it with the one
from the Silurian ship.

749
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:04,080
I send this craft off emitting
the signal they're looking for,

750
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,360
the missiles will follow.

751
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:09,880
Hopefully, Silurian ship's safe,
dinosaurs safe, everybody's safe.

752
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:13,240
Bit tight for time, though, shouldn't
really be chatting. Nefi, let's go.

753
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:16,240
How remiss of me. Almost forgot.
The thing about missiles,

754
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:19,720
very literal.
This is what they latch on to.

755
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:22,560
Now, one press of this
and the ship's demagnetised.

756
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:25,240
Doctor, whatever you want,
I can get it for you.

757
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,960
Whatever object you desire.

758
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:30,320
Did the Silurians beg you to stop?

759
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:35,960
Look, Solomon, the missiles.

760
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:39,000
See them shine?
See how valuable they are?

761
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:42,760
-And they're all yours.
-You wouldn't leave me, Doctor!

762
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,640
Enjoy your bounty.

763
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,200
Doctor!

764
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:01,280
(ALARM BLARING)

765
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:08,040
Doctor!

766
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:15,880
(LOW GROWLING)

767
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,760
So, dinosaur drop-off time.

768
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:32,600
RORY: Actually, we think home for us.

769
00:42:35,280 --> 00:42:36,320
Oh.

770
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:39,400
-Fine. Of course.
-Not forever. Just a couple of months.

771
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:42,640
Right, yes. I'm pretty busy, anyway.
I mean, I've got to drop everyone back.

772
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,520
About that.

773
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,360
Can I ask a favour?

774
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:49,520
There's something I want to see.

775
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:52,320
Oh.

776
00:43:46,600 --> 00:43:48,520
More postcards from your dad.

777
00:43:48,600 --> 00:43:50,720
Do you know what?
I think it is the fitting.

778
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:19,600
Our Father who art in Heaven,
hallowed be Thy name, Thy kingdom come,

779
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:23,400
Thy will be done.

780
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:28,520
DOCTOR: The gunslinger is a cyborg,
half man, half machine.

781
00:44:29,480 --> 00:44:33,000
-You're really letting him do this?
-Save us all? Yeah, I really am.

782
00:44:38,840 --> 00:44:42,520
Everyone who isn't an American,
drop your gun.

